{"level":50,"time":1776488728605,"pid":746703,"hostname":"interstellar","module":"db.sqlite","err":{"type":"Error","message":"database or disk is full","stack":"SQLiteError: database or disk is full\n    at run (unknown)\n    at #run (bun:sqlite:185:20)\n    at query (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/db/adapters/sqlite.ts:87:29)\n    at query (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/db/connection.ts:111:26)\n    at createWorkflowEvent (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/db/workflow-events.ts:45:16)\n    at <anonymous> (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/core/src/workflows/store-adapter.ts:49:31)\n    at executeNodeInternal (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/workflows/src/dag-executor.ts:961:12)\n    at async <anonymous> (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/workflows/src/dag-executor.ts:2754:28)\n    at async executeDagWorkflow (/mnt/ext-fast/archon/packages/workflows/src/dag-executor.ts:2428:40)\n    at async executeWorkflow (unknown)\n    at async workflowRunCommand (unknown)\n    at async main (unknown)\n    at processTicksAndRejections (native:7:39)","code":"SQLITE_FULL","errno":13,"byteOffset":-1},"sql":"INSERT INTO remote_agent_workflow_events (id, workflow_run_id, event_type, step_index, step_name, data)\n       VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)","params":["2a5745ee-8d27-4066-8c8c-8e2fcbde04ca","2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7","tool_called",null,"report","{\"tool_name\":\"Write\",\"tool_input\":{\"file_path\":\"/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7/completion-report.md\",\"content\":\"# Completion Report: Issue #280\\n\\n**Date**: 2026-04-18T07:00:00Z\\n**Workflow ID**: 2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7\\n**PR**: #626 (https://github.com/alexsiri7/reli/pull/626)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nIssue #280 required extending the inline quick-add form in the Sidebar with two optional fields: a check-in date picker and a parent project selector. The implementation extended `store.ts` (`createThing` signature) and `Sidebar.tsx` (state, form JSX, and submit handler). All validation passed (lint, 255 tests, build). A five-agent review identified 10 findings; all CRITICAL and HIGH findings were fixed in the self-review pass, 2 of 3 MEDIUM findings were fixed (date ISO conversion test and parent selector visibility tests), and 1 MEDIUM plus all 4 LOW findings were deferred.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Classification\\n\\n| Field | Value |\\n|-------|-------|\\n| Type | ENHANCEMENT |\\n| Complexity | LOW |\\n| Confidence | HIGH |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What Was Done\\n\\n### Investigation/Planning\\n\\nThe backend already supported `checkin_date` on `ThingCreate` and a `POST /api/things/relationships` endpoint — no backend changes were needed. The plan extended the existing quick-add state and form in `Sidebar.tsx` and the `createThing` store action.\\n\\n### Implementation\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `frontend/src/store.ts` | UPDATE | Added `checkinDate?: string \\\\| null` parameter to `createThing` interface and implementation; included in POST body as `checkin_date` |\\n| `frontend/src/components/Sidebar.tsx` | UPDATE | Added `quickAddCheckinDate` and `quickAddParentId` state; extended submit handler with date ISO conversion, relationship POST (with `res.ok` check), and `fetchThings` refresh; added date picker and parent project selector inputs to form JSX |\\n\\n### Validation\\n\\n| Check | Result |\\n|-------|--------|\\n| Type check | ✅ |\\n| Lint | ✅ (0 new errors; 3 pre-existing warnings) |\\n| Tests | ✅ (255 passed, 0 failed) |\\n| Build | ✅ |\\n\\n### Review & Self-Fix\\n\\n- **Findings**: 10 total from 5 review agents (1 CRITICAL, 2 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM, 4 LOW)\\n- **Fixed (CRITICAL/HIGH)**: 3\\n  - Added `vi.mock('../api', ...)` to `Sidebar.test.tsx` — relationship POST path now testable\\n  - Added `fetchThings: vi.fn()` to `calendarDefaults` mock\\n  - Added `if (!relRes.ok) throw new Error(...)` after relationship POST — matches codebase convention\\n- **Fixed (MEDIUM)**: 2\\n  - Added test asserting check-in date is passed as ISO string to `createThing`\\n  - Added tests for parent selector visibility (shown for task sections, hidden for project sections)\\n- **Skipped**: 1 MEDIUM (double `fetchThings` invocation — `createThing` already calls it internally; accepted as harmless at current scale)\\n- **Deferred**: 4 LOW\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Unaddressed Items\\n\\n### Skipped\\n\\n| Finding | Severity | Reason |\\n|---------|----------|--------|\\n| Double `fetchThings()` invocation | MEDIUM | `createThing` calls `fetchThings` internally; Sidebar also calls it after the relationship POST. Two round trips but harmless at current scale; a real fix requires refactoring `createThing` out of scope |\\n\\n### Deferred (LOW)\\n\\n| Finding | Severity | Reason |\\n|---------|----------|--------|\\n| Hardcoded `/api` URL prefix in Sidebar | LOW | Accepted for now; consistent with how other components use `apiFetch` directly |\\n| Date timezone edge case in negative UTC offsets | LOW | `T00:00:00` suffix is already applied to preserve local midnight; backend stores as `DATE` type so sub-day precision is irrelevant |\\n| Missing comment explaining `T00:00:00` timezone trick | LOW | A comment was added inline (`// Append local midnight...`) during self-fix pass |\\n| Escape key state reset not covered by test | LOW | Escape path is straightforward state-reset; deferred to a future test improvement PR |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Suggested Follow-up Issues\\n\\n| Title | Priority | Description |\\n|-------|----------|-------------|\\n| \\\"Refactor createThing to skip internal fetchThings when caller will refresh\\\" | P3 | `createThing` always fires `fetchThings` internally. When the caller also needs to refresh (e.g. after setting a parent relationship), this causes a double round-trip. Refactor to accept an optional `skipRefresh` flag. |\\n| \\\"Replace hardcoded /api prefix in Sidebar with exported BASE constant\\\" | P3 | Sidebar currently uses `'/api/things/relationships'` directly. Export `BASE` from `store.ts` or `api.ts` so it can be reused without the magic string. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Artifacts\\n\\n| Artifact | Path |\\n|----------|------|\\n| Plan | `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7/plan.md` |\\n| Implementation | `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7/implementation.md` |\\n| Validation | `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7/validation.md` |\\n| Consolidated Review | `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/2f4bab79a67b16dab17a1e09b36befa7/review/consolidated-review.md` |\\n\"}}"],"msg":"db.sqlite_query_failed"}
